# Improving DevOps Suite with AI-DLC Methodology

Based on the [AWS AI-DLC blog](https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/devops/ai-driven-development-life-cycle/) and the [AI-DLC white paper](https://prod.d13rzhkk8cj2z0.amplifyapp.com/).

## Key Insights from AI-DLC

| AI-DLC Concept | Gap in Our Current Suite |
|----------------|--------------------------|
| **3 Phases** (Inception → Construction → Operations) | Our files treat DevOps as flat; no phase-aware guidance |
| **AI as orchestrator** (proposes plans, humans validate) | Current rules are passive guardrails; no agentic patterns |
| **Persistent context** across phases | No rule for maintaining context artifacts in the repo |
| **Domain-First design** (logic → NFRs → IaC) | Missing from our workflow sequence |
| **Bolts** (hours/days, not weeks) | No workflow for rapid iteration cycles |
| **Mob Elaboration / Mob Construction** | No collaborative rituals documented |
| **AI-driven Operations** (anomaly detection, runbook automation) | [incident-response.md](file:///c:/Users/MEET%20SONI/Documents/Repos/AI-Tools/.windsurf/workflows/incident-response.md) is manual; no AI-driven ops patterns |
| **Brown-field elevation** (existing code → semantic models) | No skill for onboarding existing codebases |

